          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The cloud chamber 30 cm in diameter and 8 cm",
                " high operated in an auxillary magnetic field of",
                " intensity ~ 10.5 x 10**3 Oe = 8.36 x 10**5 A/m."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The cloud chamber was filled with oxygen in a mixture",
                " with water and alcohol vapors (in a ratio of 3 : 1",
                " by volume) to a pressure of 265 mm Hg. With a",
                " mixture of this composition, the number of impurity",
                " nuclei (carbon) in the chamber was no greater than",
                " 4% of the number of oxygen nuclei. The relative",
                " stopping power of the mixture was 0.29 for slow",
                " protons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " With the relative stopping power of the cloud",
                "  chamber mixture the recoil nuclei produced in the",
                "  (g,p), (g,n), and (g,pn) reactions have ranges up",
                "  to 20 mm and are not scattered very strongly. This",
                "  permits not only the identification of all those",
                "  reactions but also the measurement of emission",
                "  angles and the recoiling ranges."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
